cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.DS 

The paper discusses the representational power of neural networks and polynomial kernels, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also mentions the use of these techniques in computer vision (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS), which further supports these sub-categories.
